sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K090004
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Expresses KDP Potassium ATPase in Stationary Phase
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Stationary phase promoter OsmY J45992 linked to strong RBS B0030, causing expression of KDP Potassium ATPase. Also has strong artifical terminator B1002
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Must not be expressed too strongly as this would lead to toxicity issues. Choice of RBS important.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Ellis O'Neill

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0030
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Strong RBS based on Ron Weiss thesis. Strength is considered relative to <bb_part>BBa_B0031</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0032</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0033</bb_part>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix ("orig" in figure 4-14 of Ron Weiss thesis).

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B1002
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Bidirectional, with the reverse estimated to be less effective than the forward. Has a polyA tail of 6 residues.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Haiyao Huang

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K090003
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The KDP operon from E.coli, without the regulatory subunits. Pumps K+ ions into cells, against their concentration gradient, using ATP.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Primers designed to only PCR A,B,C and F subunits, removing D and E regulatory subunits.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Ellis O'Neill
